				<td colspan="2"><span>Only getting to play every 7-10 days, I stayed up until 3 this morning after a circumstance that went like this .......
<br />

<br />
Get an invitation to a *gasp* pick-up group camping the Justice exit. Being a glutton for potential punishment (prerequisite for bardic duty), I run on out and join up.
<br />

<br />
I ask if we have a 'chanter (to be polite - some get all hissy if you start mezzing add's without talking to them first), and I'm told- nope; don't need one, we are getting single pulls.
<br />

<br />
Okie. Well, I'll load mez *just in case*.  &lt;aside - we all know what happens next, right?&gt;
<br />

<br />
Sure 'nuff, get the long pull message, and then a few seconds later the short &quot;Add&quot;. I move down the hall to see the incoming, let the first go by, target the second and start mez, then here comes a third just as the I finish the first mez song, target, rinse, repeat.
<br />

<br />
Along the way we got some rats as well, and after the hall was cleared out, I say &quot;So is the puller testing me to see if I can count?&quot; get a good natured laughing comeback from ranger-boy, and then the healer says &quot; ... I don't know how bards do it .... but I am GLAD they do!&quot;
<br />

<br />
I was hooked. I stayed until the group broke up ... besides having fun, a performer ***loves*** an appreciative audience.
<br />

<br />
Trusong OneFaith</span></td>
