				<td colspan="2"><span>During a hard EF LDoN yesterday I was told that I &quot;am their hero&quot; by about 3 or 4 people.  
<br />

<br />
1 was out of group (was a guildy's alt, who was playing their bard alt and realised how much I do :p).
<br />
1 was in group, the shammy, because I proved that entrance drop rate is way better then else where (we had a reeeeally bad run of luck, and had to get about 18 in an hour.. on a collect 20).
<br />
1 was in group, the cleric, because I only brought singles for the entire duration of the LDoN.  Asides from the very beginning (no pulling room, and then wanderers came up too).  Mind you, he didn't down right say it, but he was right beside me IRL and was absolutely shocked we managed to win.
<br />

<br />
I was told I was awesome by the mages (we had 2) (ok, so, only 1 said I was awesome) and he started singing 'Did any one ever tell me you're my heroOo...'  
<br />

<br />

<br />
Ego++!  Now I get to claim that I'm a hero<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.
<br />

<br />

<br />
The best part about the whole thing was winning on a nail scrape (2, 3 minutes left?), finding a named on track, named dropping an item that's only usable by the bard and warrior... and then rolling 958.  I felt kinda guilty about taking it away from the warrior (who really, really needs some gear upgrades) but oh well.
<br />

<br />
About that...  What the flipping heck is an Elven ring doing in Miragul's?  It has absolutely no reason to be in there.  Miragul was a flipping ERUDITE!  He didn't do anything elfly at all.  He went from Odus, to Qeynos, to Evefrost. Couldn't they have named it something like &quot;A band of frozen mana&quot; or something?  Sheesh!  (For those who wonder what I'm talking about, &quot;A lost ancient elven ring&quot; or something very similar).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
