				<td colspan="2"><span>Hehe, first off I know what you mean, when a bard shines a bard REALLY shines and when people comment it feels great.
<br />

<br />
Second of all, why the heck wouldn;t he have an elven ring on... just look at us, we have a hodge podge of cool gear from all over the world, because we want the best we can get.  Miragul would be the same way =)
<br />

<br />
And lastly, yes, I have more proof about the drop rate near the entrance...  2 of the last half dozen hard LDoNs we have done were really close.  We had skipped a room or two near the entrance to delve deeper in hopes of finding a named on track, and found ourselves behind the power curve for our collections.  Both times with under 15 minutes left I suggested we return to the rooms I had skipped pulling.  One time we needed 5 items, ther other time we needed 4.  Both times we were having an average drop rate one 1 item per 4 mobs, horrendous when you have under 15 minutes and need so many items still (collect 29s suck in a hard LDoN btw).  Both times we won our dungeons, the last time we had under 1 minute left, it was crazy... when we finally reached the room we had about 9 minutes showing, and needed 4 items... only 5 mobs in the room... I get a crit fail (first of the night) and die in the doorway... load - rez - try again.  I get 2 mobs, no sweat, except it was really 3, one was a caster I didn;t see and nuked me to death from behind the door... group flees and zones out and back in, load - rez - try again, 6 minutes left, 3 items (they killed one before fleeing.)  I pull with just char buff on, I get 2 (tense and making mistakes at this point) I die, tank does his thing, cleric rezzes me right away, I mezz while I loot, LOL... not healed yet ot anything... join fight, die to ripostes (stupid me).  Sooo... group finishes killing and I get rezzed mid battle again (I think i missed a pull, i did manage a single along the way, these are the final 2 mobs in the room) timer showing 1 minute as the mob dies, I loot not knowing they had already looted one more, we win... very very very shocked, since usually 1 min on timer means end of dungeon right then and there... gave us an extra few secs that time <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />   
<br />

<br />
Soooo, long story short, tired and tense bards without buffs die easily, but hey, if we die and win, thats all that matters... and returning to the entrance area gave us the drops we needed <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /></span></td>
