				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Still kinda unfortunate that no one really does assassination or rescue if they can avoid it. 
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I love assasinates, their just a slaughter with a bonus named at the end.
<br />

<br />
Rescues... just on base principle I refuse to except a rescue. 
<br />
What do we have.. some newb that wandered into a zone way to high for him and as a result became lost and scared hiding in a corner waiting for a rescue party. IF you rescue him he will just turn around and go get lost in the same zone again anyways whats the point? 
<br />

<br />
Back on topic.
<br />
Bards have always been the superhero of Norrath.. fromthe day we glided across terrain in a graceful flight of pink sparkle rings to today.
<br />
My guild was in VT a couple of weeks ago and we were slugging along with 2 bards and 2 enchanters. We were recovering from a series of 10+ pulls that had drained everyone to near exhaustion .. the continuous battle had went for over 30 min at this point when suddenly there were 18 mobs in the raid force and both chanters went down instantenously. 
<br />
Panic set in.. clerics started camping out, paladins and SK's were taking one for the team and gathering agro. I started mezz'ing and cycling in chorus of marr to gather agro, then I kept mezz'ing.. and only had time to notice the only other bard there was doing the same. Neither of us knew exactly what happened or how we did what we did.. but 20 minutes later clerics were logging back in because the Bards had saved the raid and there were only 2 mobs in camp. How did we do it.. super hero's to the end !! Wonder twin powers activate form of !!! Your Saviour!!! 
<br />
Seriously.. sometimes we even amaze ourselves. </span></td>
